_exec_summary.SummaryText:
The Ripon facility is regulated under the Clean Air Act Amendments, also referred to as the federal RMP and the CalARP Program, due to on-site ammonia storage capacity in excess of the federal RMP applicability threshold.  RC facility produces power from natural gas, which uses anhydrous ammonia to reduce Nitrogen Oxides (NOx) emissions in its boiler exhaust and as an air coolant for its gas turbine.
The facility is located in the city of Ripon at 944 South Stockton Avenue, within the San Joaquin Valley region of California, approximately 90 miles east of San Francisco.  The facility site occupies approximately 1 acre, and is contiguous with an existing paper mill facility owned and operated by Fox River Paper Company.  
The Risk Management Plan at the RC facility is comprised of the following elements:
?Proper operation and maintenance of all system equipment;
?Comprehensive employee training; 
?A written emergency response plan;
?Documented safety procedures for employees and contractors;
?Inclusion of ammonia specific health, safety, and response data in the RMP; and 
?Use of chemical specific monitors and mitigation systems to detect and mitigate potential releases. 
As part of its effort to protect the employees and the environment at the site, RC has, and will continue to:
?Make every effort to keep the workplace free of recognized hazards likely to cause injury to employees, the public, or the environment;
?Train employees in safe and environmentally conscious practices and require compliance with environmental, health, and safety (EHS) regulations, policies, and procedures;
?Provide professional staff to maintain and support EHS programs; and
?Fully comply with laws regulating Environmental Protection and Employee Health and Safety.
